cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep neural networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed loss term aims to improve the discriminative power of the learned representations, which is a key aspect of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of off-the-shelf architectures, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on a benchmark dataset, which is a common practice in neural networks (cs.NE).
